{"ts":"2026-06-25T23:03:32.990Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Structuring Local Content**\n\nI'm focused on structuring a local static content database now. The initial design will incorporate querying across key industries like Financial Services, Health Sciences, and Public Service. This initial structural approach aims for precise and targeted search results.\n\n\n**Organizing Categories & Structure**\n\nI'm now diving into categorizing and structuring the specific content types. I am thinking about how industries align with build tools; for instance, \"Insurance AI\" fits into both \"Industries / Financial Services\" and \"Build With GFF.\" \"Build With GFF\" is shaping up as a crucial element, acting as the nexus for specific build guides. Resources like articles, videos, podcasts, and company details will be essential. My goal is a static dataset with well-defined records.\n\n\n**Designing Search Behavior**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the user experience of the search feature. My focus is an AI-concierge style interaction: a conversational-looking prompt box with glassmorphism, instant results, subtle glow, and smooth transitions. The UI will feature clickable example prompts and a premium, clean search input design. I'm prioritizing immediate results displaying title, category, description, and link, all appearing instantly.\n\n\n**Refining Search Interface Design**\n\nI'm now iterating on the visual design of the search feature's UI. I'm aiming for a sophisticated \"AI-concierge\" aesthetic, with clickable example prompts to streamline the search experience. The initial prompt input will be elegant, with subtle visual cues such as a light border and a clean icon, and the results will be displayed in an elegant list or grid, with category tags. I'm making sure that the empty state is equally polished, offering helpful suggestions when no matches are found. The whole design is leaning into a clean, premium, minimal look.\n\n\n**Defining Visual Attributes**\n\nI'm now focusing on the visual theme. I'm leaning toward a dark mode design with a black background (`#010101`), subtle white borders (`white/5` or `white/10`), and blue/red gradients based on primary and accent colors from the header (`#E4000F`, `#009DFF`). I'm also ensuring that the search examples yield the exact desired results, starting with \"Build AI for Banking.\"\n\n\n**Mapping Content Fields**\n\nI'm now mapping out specific content fields and keywords for entries. I've defined entries like \"Trust and Regulated Financial Teams,\" \"Create University AI Lab,\" and \"AI Labs,\" each with title, category, description, links, and relevant keywords. I am working on how to classify the search query. I'm focusing on consistency in this approach.\n\n\n**Expanding Content Coverage**\n\nI'm currently expanding content, focusing on \"Insurance AI & Policy Automation\" with corresponding fields and keywords. I've also added \"Mining AI & Resource Optimization\" to broaden the scope. I am ensuring that the categories align with the existing structure. I am working to ensure that the descriptions are clear and concise, with optimal keywords. I've added a Financial Services & Trust entry to enhance the dataset.\n\n\n**Adding Industry Categories**\n\nI've just added several entries, including \"Industry & Natural Resources,\" focusing on AI-driven workflows, and \"Retail AI & Commerce Engines\" to broaden coverage in \"Build With GFF.\" I've ensured relevant keywords and descriptions for precise search results. I am also working on categorizing more content entries that will be mapped into the database.\n\n\n**Indexing New Data**\n\nI'm now indexing new data for a more complete static search. I've added entries for \"Build AI GCC\" under \"Build With GFF,\" focusing on Global Capability Centers. I'm also adding \"AI Strategy\" and \"AI Engineering\" under \"Capabilities,\" with descriptions and relevant keywords