index is well-aligned with GFF AI branding and existing navigational elements, with no issues detected so far.\n\n\n**Designing Search Interface**\n\nI'm now refining the search interface's design to incorporate a \"concierge\" search experience. I am designing a sleek chat command box input with glowing effects, a search icon, and a clear button. I'm adding example tags below for common queries, making them clickable for instant search. I'm considering both a curated default state and instant results based on the search query.\n\n\n**Designing Search States**\n\nI'm now determining the optimal user experience for the search interface. I'm choosing between a default state with curated quick starts or a clean initial state with instructional text. I'm prioritizing a polished empty state when no matches are found, and a gorgeous, responsive grid layout for search results. My goal is a clean, visually appealing design, avoiding unnecessary clutter, and ensuring mobile responsiveness. I'll focus on clean typography, delicate border lines, thin icons, and clear space to improve the user experience.\n\n\n\n**Implementing Search Components**\n\nI'm now implementing the search components. I'm focusing on responsiveness across devices, ensuring padding and text sizes adapt. I'm also ensuring that `motion` from `motion/react` is working. I've imported standard Lucide icons such as `Search`, `Sparkles`, `X`, and `ArrowRight`. I'm also now designing the search-matching logic, focusing on fuzzy search with normalization. I'm working on the design for empty and default states.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Search Algorithms**\n\nI'm now scoring and sorting search results for a premium user experience. I'm prioritizing exact title matches, then category matches, and finally, keyword and description matches. I'll limit results to six items to avoid clutter, displayed elegantly. I'll implement the database as a local array for speed, focusing on clean integration within the file. I am looking